Perfect. Now I have all the information I need to provide a comprehensive report.

## Organization Invite Functionality - Complete Code Walkthrough

Based on my thorough search of the codebase, here's how the organization invite system works end-to-end:

### 1. **Database Schema** (`/Users/rafa/Obsession/rudel/packages/sql-schema/src/auth-schema.ts`)

The `invitation` table stores invite records:
```typescript
export const invitation = pgTable("invitation", {
	id: text("id").primaryKey(),
	organizationId: text("organization_id")
		.notNull()
		.references(() => organization.id, { onDelete: "cascade" }),
	email: text("email").notNull(),
	role: text("role"),
	status: text("status").notNull().default("pending"),
	expiresAt: timestamp("expires_at", {...}).notNull(),
	inviterId: text("inviter_id")
		.notNull()
		.references(() => user.id, { onDelete: "cascade" }),
	createdAt: timestamp("created_at", {...}).defaultNow().notNull(),
	teamId: text("team_id"),
});
```

Additional tables: `organization`, `member`, `user` schemas also shown in the same file.

### 2. **Frontend - Organization Management Page** (`/Users/rafa/Obsession/rudel/apps/web/src/pages/dashboard/OrganizationPage.tsx`)

**UI Components:**
- Invite form with email input and role selector (member/admin)
- Shows generated invite link after sending
- Displays list of current members with role badges
- Shows pending invitations with cancel option
- Organization rename functionality
- Delete organization (danger zone)

**Key Functions:**
```typescript
const handleInvite = async (e: React.FormEvent) => {
	const res = await authClient.organization.inviteMember({
		email: inviteEmail.trim(),
		role: inviteRole as "member" | "admin",
	});
	if (res.data) {
		const link = `${window.location.origin}/invitation/${res.data.id}`;
		setInviteLink(link);
		setInviteEmail("");
		invalidate();
	}
};

const handleCancelInvitation = async (invitationId: string) => {
	await authClient.organization.cancelInvitation({ invitationId });
	invalidate();
};

const handleRemoveMember = async (memberIdOrEmail: string) => {
	await authClient.organization.removeMember({ memberIdOrEmail });
	invalidate();
};
```

### 3. **Frontend - Invitation Acceptance Pages**

**Invitations List Page** (`/Users/rafa/Obsession/rudel/apps/web/src/pages/dashboard/InvitationsPage.tsx`)
- Shows all pending invitations for the logged-in user
- "Accept" and "Decline" buttons for each invitation
- Displays organization name, role, and invite date

```typescript
const handleAccept = async (invitationId: string) => {
	const res = await authClient.organization.acceptInvitation({
		invitationId,
	});
	if (res.data) {
		await switchOrg(res.data.member.organizationId);
	}
	invalidate();
};

const handleDecline = async (invitationId: string) => {
	await authClient.organization.rejectInvitation({ invitationId });
	invalidate();
};
```

**Standalone Invitation Page** (`/Users/rafa/Obsession/rudel/apps/web/src/pages/AcceptInvitationPage.tsx`)
- Accessed via `/invitation/{invitationId}` route
- If user not logged in, redirects to login with return URL
- Shows accept/decline UI
- Success message and redirect to dashboard on accept

```typescript
const handleAccept = async () => {
	const res = await authClient.organization.acceptInvitation({
